  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd6\u0dbd\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d85\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc1\u0ddd\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Financial Fund requests information including revision of electricity bill",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Another round of talks between President Ranil Wickremesinghe and the International Monetary Fund was held at the President's Office this afternoon (26) with the aim of finding solutions to the ongoing financial crisis.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe joined the discussion through Zoom technology and the two sides exchanged views positively, the President's Office says.",
        "In accordance with the request made by the representatives of the International Monetary Fund to provide additional information necessary for these discussions regarding the revision of the electricity bill and the Excise Act, it was also agreed to provide the information by next Monday.",
        "Financial advisers and legal advisers of the International Monetary Fund also joined the discussion today and it was decided to hold another round of discussions next Wednesday (31).",
        "Head of the International Monetary Fund's Discussion Board Peter Breuer, Deputy Head Osairo Kosaiko, Permanent Representative of the International Monetary Fund Mr. Tobagans and Chief of Staff to the President and Senior Advisor to the President on National Security Sagala Ratnayake, President's Secretary Saman Ekanayake, Central Bank Governor Dr. Mr. Nandalal Weerasinghe and senior officials of the Central Bank including the Treasury Secretary participated in the discussion."
      ],
